        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 10:54PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1053 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northwest of Verdigris, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
New Alluwe...                     Adair...
Vinita...                         Verdigris...
Claremore...                      Big Cabin...
Oologah...                        Chelsea...
White Oak...                      Foyil...
Bushyhead...                      Tiawah...
Owasso...                         Catoosa...
Collinsville...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 237 and 290.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
